    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis is a duplicate of https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/20306, but that issue is closed and it's still an issue or has got broken again since then, as commented there by @mawkler.\r\n\r\nIn neovide we get the following logs\r\n```\r\nERROR [neovide::error_handling] Could not parse event from neovim: invalid event format for event 'grid_cursor_goto' -\r\n [Integer(PosInt(3)), Integer(NegInt(-1)), Integer(PosInt(0))] - invalid u64 format -1\r\nNeovide panicked with the message 'Could not parse event from neovim: invalid event format for event 'grid_cursor_goto\r\n' - [Integer(PosInt(3)), Integer(NegInt(-1)), Integer(PosInt(0))] - invalid u64 format -1'. (File: src/error_handling.\r\n```\r\nSo, it sends `grid_cursor_goto` with `grid: 2, row: -1, column: 0`, the row is negative, which it shouldn't be.\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `neovide --nofork -- --clean -c 'set cmdheight=0' -c \"=vim.keymap.set('n', '/', 'ms/', { silent = true })\"`\r\n2. Press `/p`\r\n3. Neovide crashes with the (logged) message: `Could not parse event from neovim: invalid u64 format -1`\r\n\r\n> **Neovim version**: v0.10.0-dev-735+g8fe9f41f7 **Neovide version**: 0.10.4\r\n>\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should always send positive cursor positions.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.0-dev-735+g8fe9f41f7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nManjaro Linux x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNeovide version**: 0.10.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
